            {
              "identifier": "1611770416833433600",
              "commentcount": "204",
              "articlebody": "In gas cars, the engine at the front of the vehicle gets pushed inside the cabin during a collision—like walking into a wall with a pile of bricks in front of you. As EVs don’t have engines,...",

            },
            {
              "identifier": "1611768486346526720",
              "commentcount": "124",
              "articlebody": "Sometimes a crash is unavoidable. In that case, the crumple zones, structural integrity & low center of gravity present in every Tesla can help to reduce the risk of injury, cabin intrusion...",

              "url": "https://twitter.com/Tesla/status/1611768486346526720"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "1611768484060626944",
              "commentcount": "50",
              "articlebody": "We continuously improve safety features long after a car has been delivered via over-the-air software updates. For example—using Tesla Vision, your Tesla is now able to deploy the seatbelt...",

            },
            {
              "identifier": "1611768482105802752",
              "commentcount": "70",
              "articlebody": "If there’s a vehicle or obstacle in your blind spot, your vehicle will alert you with visual & audible feedback. These features come standard with every Tesla.",

              "position": "17",

              "url": "https://twitter.com/Tesla/status/1611768482105802752"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "1611768480537116672",
              "commentcount": "66",
              "articlebody": "Among other benefits, active safety features are designed to help you avoid unintended lane departures and alert or brake in case of a potential forward collision—avoiding or reducing its severity.",

              "position": "18",
              "datecreated": "2023-01-07T16:55:25.000Z",
